ce:section.ce:para:
To confirm the practicality and accuracy of this approach in real samples, we tested the SO2 residues in four previously mentioned MFHMs. The samples were extracted using an acid distillation method and the SO2 absorption liquids were detected with our proposed method. The SO2 residues in the four MFHMs were calculated to be 16.6, 0.7, 171.8, and 183.6 g/kg, respectively (Table 1
                        ). The method’s accuracy was estimated via the spike-recovery experiments by adding 120, 240 and 360 μM of HSO3
                        − to the sample solution. Table 1 shows that the recoveries ranged from 86.5 % to 112.4 %, with corresponding relative standard deviations (RSDs) of less than 1.9 %, indicating this method’s good accuracy. Furthermore, the MFHM samples were detected by titration method as well. These results from the titration method agreed well with those from our proposed methods, which further prove the accuracy and feasibility of the CECDs-Cr (VI)-based method in the determination of sulfite residues in real samples.
